<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="22" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Ewing</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-16"><hi rend="italic">February 16,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 103.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch. No. 97 B, of
                            the 11th ultimo, relative to the prohibition of the importation of
                            American cattle into Belgium, I inclose for your information a copy of
                            correspondence between the Belgian legation at this capital and the
                                Department<note n="1" xml:id="d22fn1">See <ref target="#pg_27">page
                                    27</ref>, and <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> with regard
                            to the subject.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>